CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 14 reads: "New Honor Society Members - These students were initiated into Westinghouse High School's chapter of the National Honor Society, Jan. 9. Left to right, seated: Patricia Colangelo, Yvonne Thomas, Patricia Amen, Inez Bailey, Bonita Smith and Joyce Boulden.  Standing: Mary Metzger, Paul Ross, David Truxal, Lorraine Fuller, Bonnie Hetrick, Nelson Harrison, Patricia McCoy, Grayson Howard and Carl Hancock.  Not shown is Roger Parrish who was also initiated at the ceremony. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: National Honor Society members, seated from left: Patricia Colangelo, Yvonne Thomas, Patricia Amen, Inez Bailey, Bonita Smith, Joyce Boulden; standing: Mary Metzger, Paul Ross, David Truxal, Lorraine Fuller, Bonnie Hetrick, Nelson Harrison, Patricia McCoy, Grayson Howard, and Carl Hancock, gathered in interior, possibly Westinghouse High School, with dark sofa, Mayan inspired patterned curtains, and dark linoleum floor
